Albertsons Ranks 53rd in Fortune 2024: A Detailed Analysis

In the latest Fortune 2024 ranking, Albertsons Companies, Inc. (ACI) secured the 53rd position, maintaining its standing from the previous year with a zero change in rank. As a prominent player in the Food & Drug Stores sector and industry, Albertsons continues to demonstrate its resilience in the competitive retail landscape.

Founded by Joe Albertson in 1939, the company has undergone significant transformations over the years, with Vivek Sankaran currently at the helm as CEO. Sankaran, who is not the founder of the company, brings valuable expertise to the position, guiding the organization towards continued growth and success. Notably, Albertsons has a male CEO, and its leadership does not feature a female CEO.

One of the key highlights of Albertsons' performance is its growth in jobs, which reflects the company's commitment to expanding its workforce and contributing to the overall economy. With a significant employee base of 198,650, Albertsons is one of the largest employers in the industry.

As of March 28, 2024, Albertsons' market value stood at $12.35 billion, with a later update on August 5, 2024, reporting a market value of $11.33 billion. The company's revenues for the fiscal year ended February 28, 2024, were $77.65 billion, representing an 8% increase from the previous year. However, profits declined by 6.6% to $1.51 billion during the same period. Albertsons' assets were valued at $26.17 billion, underscoring the company's robust financial foundation.

As a public company, Albertsons is headquartered in Boise, Idaho, and is listed on the stock exchange under the ticker symbol ACI. The company's global presence is acknowledged by its inclusion in the Fortune Global 500 list. Although it did not make it to the World's Most Admired Companies or the Best Companies to Work For lists, Albertsons' stable ranking and financial performance indicate its position as a reliable player in the retail sector.

Overall, Albertsons' steady performance in the Fortune 2024 ranking is a testament to the company's ability to navigate the complexities of the retail industry. As the company continues to evolve and adapt to changing market conditions, it is likely to remain a significant player in the Food & Drug Stores sector.